description.full:
Draw blood for clinical laboratory evaluations for all subjects. For any subject who has an aspartate transaminase [AST/SGOT] or alanine transaminase [ALT/SGPT] values greater than or equal to 3 time upper limit of normal (ULN), alkaline phosphatase values > 2 times ULN, total bilirubin levels > 1.5 times ULN, serum potassium level < 4 mmol/L or greater than ULN (defined by the testing laboratory), serum calcium level outside the reference range (defined by the testing laboratory), and/or serum magnesium level outside the reference range (defined by the testing laboratory) at any visit other than visit 1, the subject must return to the study site for a repeat Complete Blood Count (CBC) with differential (for decreased ANC values), comprehensive metabolic panel (for elevated Liver Function Tests [LFTs]), or serum potassium/calcium/magnesium 5 to 7 days after that visit.
Collect urine for laboratory evaluations.

Footnote.footnoteText: Applicable only to subjects who received study drug (dose) for XX-XX days.
Study drug (XXX) will be evaluated by investigator/medically qualified designee (must be MD or DO) for tolerability.
CSPCs = Clinical Supply Product Complaints; ET = early termination; F/U = follow up; Hx = history; PGIC = Patient’s Global Impression of Change.

During the prerandomization and double-blind phases, “Average Pain over the Last 24 Hours” scores will be recorded by subjects daily in the eDiary at around 8:00 pm. During the double blind phase, “Average Pain over the Last 24 Hours” scores will be recorded at the study visits, except when the subject decides to discontinue the study drug, in which case the subject should record his/her “Average Pain over the Last 24 Hours” score in the eDiary at the time of discontinuation of study drug.

During the Pre-Randomization Phase, "average pain over the last 24 hours" scores will be recorded daily in the diary at around 8pm. During the Double-blind Phase, "average pain over the last 24 hours" scores will be recorded at the study visits.
Electronic diary (eDiary) will be completed on all days during prerandomization phase and during double-blind phase.

Follow up phone call is required 5 to 7 days after the removal of the last study drug (XXX) for those subjects who DO NOT enroll in the open label extension phase according to instructions in section XX.
Follow-up phone calls will be conducted following dose adjustment (down-titration) according to instructions in section XX.
Height is included in vital signs only at visit 1.

If after XX days, the subject responded to and tolerated study drug (dose 1), he/she will proceed to Vx Randomization on the same day. If the subject did not tolerate study drug (dose 1), he/she will proceed to Vx Run-in Failure on the same day. If the subject tolerated study drug (dose 1) but did not respond to treatment, he/she will receive study drug (dose 2) for another X days.

If the subject does not tolerate study drug (dose 2) and/or his/her pain is controlled by study drug (dose 2), refer to section XX. If the subject tolerates and does not respond to study drug (dose 2), he/she will receive study drug (dose 3) for another XX (+2) days.
In addition to being recorded at each visit, “pain over the last 24 hours” will be recorded daily, using the eDiary, during the open-label titration and the double-blind periods.

In addition to being recorded at each visit, “pain right now” will be recorded before each dose of rescue supplemental medication taken, using the eDiary, for XXX pain during the open-label titration and the double-blind periods.

Once all Inclusion/Exclusion criteria (with exception of the daily pain scores) are met, the Investigator or site staff will call the subject and instruct him/her to stop all incoming analgesic medications and other medications used for chronic pain. Starting 2 days after the subject discontinued all pain medications used for chronic pain, the Investigator or the site staff will contact to the subject daily to assess the subject’s pain scores for qualification to enter the Run-in Period.
Only applicable to subjects not entering the extension phase.
Only applicable to subjects who are non-screen failures.

Patch removal and application (date/time/dose/site of application/patch adhesion) will be recorded in the eDiary, as needed, ie, whenever the subject changes the patch. Patch adhesion information should be collected after the subject has been titrated and only if a given study drug patch has been worn for less than the required 7 days. Pain scores will also be recorded in the eDiary as follows: During the screening period, “average pain over the last 24 hours” scores will be recorded daily in the eDiary at around 8 pm. During the open-label maintenance period “average pain over the last 24 hours” scores will be recorded once weekly in the eDiary at around 8 pm on the same day of the week the first patch was applied. During the dose-titration period, “pain right now” scores will be recorded in the eDiary immediately before a subject takes rescue as supplemental chronic pain medication (to be used for compliance/diversion purposes). During open-label maintenance period, supplemental analgesic medication use and “pain relief” will be recorded daily at around 8 pm in the eDiary.
Phone call by investigator/medically qualified designee (must be MD or DO, or for this evaluation, an RN may make the phone call to the subject) 5-7 days after discontinuation of study drug.
Physical examinations must be performed by investigator/medically qualified designee (must be MD or DO).
Procedures must be performed by a MD or DO.
SOWS will be conducted daily during weeks X to XX of the double blind phase.
SOWS will be conducted daily on Post-randomization Days X through XX.

Study Drug Discontinuation procedures should be performed for subjects that discontinue study-drug for any reason prior to completing all XX days of the Double-blind Phase and choose to continue to complete all remaining clinic visits and procedures. The Study Drug Discontinuation procedures should be completed as soon as possible after discontinuing study-drug. Importantly, the subject should record his/her “average pain over last 24 hours” score on his/her diary <ft:u>at the time of discontinuation of study-drug</ft:u>.

Subjects may be required to have a repeat complete blood count (CBC) with differential (for decreased ANC), comprehensive metabolic panel (for elevated liver function tests [LFTs]), and/or serum potassium/calcium/magnesium (for values outside ranges specified per protocol inclusion criterion No. XX 5 to 7 days after the visit as referenced per protocol visit procedures.
Subjects will also complete the modified SOWS on each of the first X days of the double-blind period (using the eDiary).
The PGIC will be conducted at the end of weeks XX, XX and XX or ET.
The site personnel will contact the subject 2 days before the scheduled visits according to instructions in section XX.

The site personnel will contact the subject two days before the scheduled visits to remind him/her NOT to take any supplemental analgesic medications during the 30 hour period prior to the clinic visit.

There will be a phone contact to assess the tolerability/safety of study drug (dose 1) and daily phone call(s) will occur to assess pain responses to study drug (dose 2) according to instructions in section XX.
Two readings a minimum of 10 minutes apart. Subjects may be required to have a repeat ECG after the visit at which ECG shows prolongation of QTc interval as referenced per protocol visit procedures.

Visit X/end of study evaluations should be performed for subjects that (a) complete all XX days of the Double-blind Phase or (b) discontinue study-drug prior to completing XX days and choose NOT to continue to complete all remaining clinic visits and procedures. The Visit X/End of Study procedures should be completed as soon as possible after discontinuing study-drug. Importantly, the subject should record his/her average pain.
Visit X/end of double-blind evaluations should be performed for subjects who (a) complete all XX ± 3 days of the double blind phase or (b) discontinue study drug prior to completing XX ± 3 days.
